  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount stolen and the defendant's character. Considering federal and state sentencing guidelines for first-time offenders in similar theft cases, a sentence of 6 months incarceration is appropriate to serve as a deterrent while allowing for potential rehabilitation and continued restitution.",
